div1.p:
Chown and Green 

                     pleaded guilty to the first indictment; 

                     Green not guilty to the indictments on which he was charged alone. Chown confessed to a previous conviction of felony on June 22, 1909.

Sentence, 



                     Three months' hard labour; 


                     prisoner to pay the costs of the prosecution to an amount not exceeding £25.
